cs.HC, cs.AI, cs.IR, cs.CY, cs.CL 

The paper focuses on designing an accessibility measure for webpages to draw disabled users to accessible pages. This involves using automatic web content assessors to test the validity of criteria defined by the WCAG 2.0 guidelines proposed by the World Wide Web Consortium (W3C) organization. The approach is based on the theory of belief functions, which is related to artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and human-computer interaction (cs.HC). The use of automatic web content assessors and information fusion frameworks also relates to information retrieval (cs.IR), cybersecurity (cs.CY), and natural language processing (cs.CL).
